<p>I have created a texture and filled it with purple using OpenGL ES 3.1 on Android (using the NDK). The problem is that texture lookup in the shader does not work as expected.</p>  <p>I create the texture like this:</p>  <pre><code>glGenTextures(1, &amp;mGLTexture); glBindTexture(GL_TEXTURE_2D, mGLTexture); glTexStorage2D(GL_TEXTURE_2D, 1, GL_RGBA8, textureSize.x, textureSize.y);  vector&lt;GLubyte&gt; img; int i = 0; img.resize(4 * textureSize.x * textureSize.y); for (unsigned x = 0; x &lt; 64; ++x) {     for (unsigned y = 0; y &lt; 64; ++y) {         img[i * 4 + 0] = 255;         img[i * 4 + 1] = 0;         img[i * 4 + 2] = 255;         img[i * 4 + 3] = 255;         // purple with full alpha     } }  glTexSubImage2D(GL_TEXTURE_2D, 0, 0, 0,                  64, 64,                 GL_RGBA, GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE, img.data()); </code></pre>  <p>No OpenGL errors are thrown during this process.</p>  <p>I then bind the texture:</p>  <pre><code>glActiveTexture(GL_TEXTURE0); glBindTexture(GL_TEXTURE_2D, mGLTexture); glUniform1i(texLocation, 0); // got texLocation using glGetUniformLocation </code></pre>  <p>Now, the problem occurs: In my shader, when I look up the texture only at (0,0), using <code>FragColor = texture(tex, vec2(0,0));</code> it works as expected, i.e things get painted purple.<br> For all other texture coordinates (e.g <code>vec2(0.5f,0.5f)</code>) I just get black everywhere.</p>